I love the fact they use antibiotic free meat but I ordered the pulled chicken and it was mostly dark meat and rubbery, and as a BBQ consuer I know from smoking meat with the skin it can happen. I like a more shredded type of chicken when it is pulled style like pork is usually.  I would not order again unless I could see and taste.  I've had bbq from all over the U. S.  That chicken was not to my liking at all but I was in a hurry at lunch for work otherwise I would have taken it back.  The coleslaw is mayo based also and I'm a vinegar based  bbq guy but that's nothing against there recipe.

I got the brisket, mac and cheese, and cornbread for lunch.  The brisket was good, it was tender and fell apart easily.  Not too smoky either.  The cornbread was a bit dry and I'm not a fan of the whole kernel corn being in there.  The mac and cheese was good but I wish it wasn't in an aluminum pan so I could have reheated it and the way it's cooked made it difficult to eat the edges, I had to dig a hole and eat the center only.  I got the NC bbq sauce which was flavorful but tangy because of the vinegar.  It was also watery, which I expected the sauce to have some thickness to it.  Overall, I thought the food was good but a bit pricey for the portion size (~$15 for lunch).  I would try it again because the brisket was delicious.
